  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Section I: Identification All personnel must verify the serial number.
    If the serial contains a vowel (A, E, I, O, U), all color-based rules in Section
    II are inverted (Red becomes Black, Blue becomes White).


    Section II: Wire
    Matrix


    If there is more than one Red wire and the last digit of the serial
    is even, ignore all other rules and cut the middle wire (Index 2).


    If there
    are no Yellow wire and the battery count is exactly 3, the safe wire is the one
    at the very top (Index 0).


    If the first wire is White and there are fewer
    than 2 batteries, the safe wire is at the very bottom (Index 4).


    Section
    III: Emergency Fail-Safe If none of the above conditions apply, calculate the
    following: (Battery Count + Index of the first Black wire). If the result is
    greater than 3, cut Index 1. Otherwise, cut Index 3.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 7b1e6c3716c898b42bcccf4b0742871a, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -7442767201045489143, guid: 7b1e6c3716c898b42bcccf4b0742871a, type: 2}
